pull_request.title: Fix some Windows issues in update-flutter-sdk
pull_request.body:
Some minor issues when running on Windows:

- Using `Uri.parse()` doesn't work on a Windows file path like `C:\foo\` (`Unsupported operation: Cannot extract a file path from a c URI`) so changed to `Uri.file()`
- Some calls to `flutter --version` were using `./bin/flutter` which fails on Windows (because programmatic executions require `flutter.bat`) so changed to `CliCommand.flutter`

@kenzieschmoll

issue.title: Rewrite update_flutter_sdk.sh as a Dart script
issue.body:
This addresses some of the issues for Windows users [here](https://github.com/flutter/devtools/issues/6595) by rewriting `update_flutter_sdk.sh` as a Dart script.

This PR also bumps the frequency of the `flutter-candidate-update.yaml` workflow to run twice a day instead of once a day so that the `flutter-candidate.txt` file has a smaller chance of becoming stale.

Also, work towards https://github.com/flutter/devtools/issues/6324

issue.title: MacOS not longer works with this tool
issue.body:
After upgrading flutter and launching from VSC the app crashes. 
When loading the app via CLI it works fine.

Launch config

```
  {
    "name": "Mac",
    "type": "dart",
    "request": "launch",
    "deviceId": "macOS",
    "program": "lib/main.dart",
    "args": ["flutter run -d macos"],
  },
```

`Flutter (Channel stable, 3.13.9, on macOS 14.0 23A344 darwin-arm64, locale en-NO)`

comment.body:
Are you trying to build DevTools or trying to build some other Flutter app and connect it to DevTools?

If it is the former, please follow the [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/flutter/devtools/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) instructions for running DevTools. If you open the `devtools/packages` directory in VS code, you will see many launch configurations, and then you can just select the `macOS` device from VS code and click Run to run DevTools on macos. Make sure to follow the instructions about the [workflow for making changes](https://github.com/flutter/devtools/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#workflow-for-making-changes) - there is an important step there to update your local flutter SDK `devtools_tool update-flutter-sdk --local`

Remove io import from devtools_app that was only used for tests
pull_request.body: This was getting tree shaken out of the web build so we didn't see an error, but we should not import `dart:io` under `devtools_app` unless it is for a Desktop specific implementation (usually under `config_specific/`)
